headline: Treasurys Choppy After Mixed Jobs Data
summary: U.S. Treasury yields are leaning lower but mostly choppy after Tuesday’s mixed jobs data. Yields, which fall when bond prices rise, initially dropped after the payrolls report, with traders focused on the negative aspects of the data, such as an uptick in the unemployment rate.
